The paper focuses on using machine learning techniques to address blind spots in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves training predictive models using labeled data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using image-based state representations, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of oracle feedback, which could be relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
